could perswade her to Marry him; and saith Mr. (^Hill^) , (^I shall  #
light on this^) Mountford. 
Why, said I to him, What hurt hath Mr. (^Mountford^) done you? Saith #
he, (^I have been 
Abused, and I will be Revenged^) .
   [$ (^L. H. Steward.^) $] That was (^Hill^) that said so.
   [$Mrs. (^Browne.^) $] Yes. So I went and told Mrs. (^Mountford^)  #
of it.
   [$Mr. (^Att. Gen.^) $] Pray acquaint my Lords what my Lord        #
(^Mohun^) said to you about 
